Concept decisions worth recording -- each was a real fork where the naive pick was WRONG:
- Net income = attributable to PARENT, not consolidated. ALB alone tagged three: NetIncomeLoss -0.511
  (attrib), ProfitLoss -0.465 (incl NCI), NetIncomeLossAvailableToCommonStockholdersBasic -0.677 (after
  preferred divs) -- used NetIncomeLoss. For the IFRS filers ProfitLossAttributableToOwnersOfParent !=
  ProfitLoss: SQM 0.685 vs 0.692; VALE 2.352 vs 1.983 (NCI took a loss, so the parent share is LARGER
  than consolidated). Used attributable for both.
- Capex = cash-flow capex first (PaymentsToAcquirePPE / PurchaseOfPPEClassifiedAsInvesting); PP&E-additions
  only as fallback. SQM 0.972 (cash flow) NOT 0.985 (additions, which a max-value pick had grabbed). VALE
  has no cash-flow capex tag -> IFRS PP&E additions 5.469, flagged in the row note.
- A first pass pulled Vale's net income/capex/shares from a STALE 2012 us-gaap filing because the picker
  tried us-gaap before ifrs-full and returned first-namespace-wins. Fixed to latest-period-wins, then to
  explicit priority-per-concept. Caught by printing every candidate at the reporting year before writing.

