METHOD, and the trap it avoids: every figure was read off a RENDERED crop of the consolidated statement,
never off the PDF text layer. The crops are anchored to 合并利润表 / 合并现金流量表 because each report ALSO
carries a 母公司利润表 (parent-company-only) statement with the SAME row labels and DIFFERENT numbers. An
unanchored label search grabs the parent-only figures and NOTHING COMPLAINS -- the first crop pass did
exactly that (pulled 600111 p110 and 603799/600497 p93) and was thrown away.

Internal cross-check, each inside its own filing:
- 603799 and 600497: 归属于母公司股东的净利润 + 少数股东损益 = 净利润, exactly
  (6,110,378,757.84 + 1,409,877,189.38 = 7,520,255,947.22; 1,035,324,120.59 + -20,253,320.63 = 1,015,070,799.96).
- 600111: attributable profit / basic EPS 0.6227 = 3.62bn shares, matching its share count.
600497's minority interest is NEGATIVE, so the parent's share (1.035bn) EXCEEDS consolidated net profit
(1.015bn) -- the same trap as Vale and Ganfeng. Taking the consolidated line would have understated it.

