  tagged EntityCommonStockSharesOutstanding is dated 2011, stale by fifteen years), USA Rare Earth (tagged
  count predates the FY2025 year end). A stale or wrong-entity share count yields a confidently wrong market
  cap, which is worse than a blank.

TWO COUNTERS IN THIS REPO DISAGREE, LEGITIMATELY. tools/check_data.py has_financials() counts a company as
costed if ANY of the five financial fields is set (02: 17/33). shared/build_map.py counts
`c.get("revenue_usd_b")` only (02: 16/33). The whole gap is Lithium Americas, which has net income and capex
but no revenue. Neither is wrong; they answer different questions. Recorded because a future session that
compares the gate's number to the artifact's number will otherwise think one of them is broken. The README
row now states both.

